Waste to Energy Conversion System
📌 Overview

This project focuses on developing a system that converts waste materials into electrical energy using eco-friendly and sustainable methods. The goal is to reduce environmental pollution while generating useful power from otherwise discarded resources.

The system integrates basic electronic components such as converters, sensors, and energy storage units to efficiently harvest and utilize energy from waste.

🌍 Motivation

With the rapid increase in waste generation and energy demand, traditional disposal methods lead to:

Environmental pollution
Resource wastage
Increased carbon emissions

This project aims to:

Promote clean energy solutions
Reduce dependency on conventional energy sources
Encourage sustainable waste management
⚙️ Working Principle

The system converts waste into electrical energy through a multi-stage process:

Waste Collection
Organic or mechanical waste is collected.
Energy Conversion
Waste is processed using suitable methods (e.g., mechanical, thermal, or biological conversion).
Energy is extracted in the form of electrical output.
Power Conditioning
Converters regulate and stabilize the generated energy.
Energy Storage
Batteries or capacitors store the generated electricity.
Utilization
Stored energy is used to power low-energy devices like LEDs or sensors.
🧩 System Components
Energy Conversion Unit
Voltage Converter / Regulator
Sensors (for monitoring input/output)
Energy Storage (Battery / Capacitor)
Load (LED / small devices)
